layout: base.njk
title: Presentations
permalink: /presentations/
navSlug: presentations
parentSlug: products
subtitle: Slide-deck templates and the HTML viewer / PDF / PNG pipeline.
---

<section>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="eyebrow">Presentations</div>
    <h2>Slide Deck Templates</h2>
    <p class="lede">
      The presentation generator renders Markdown into a self-contained HTML viewer, a PDF, and per-slide PNGs.
      Each slide picks a layout via an HTML-comment directive (<code>&lt;!-- @type: title --&gt;</code>).
      Slide thumbnails below are auto-regenerated from the canonical showcase deck whenever you run
      <code>npm run build:assets</code> — so this page always reflects the current state of the template.
    </p>

    <div class="action-bar">
      <a href="{{ '/previews/decks/demo-deck/' | url }}" target="_blank">Open the full demo deck →</a>
      <a href="{{ '/previews/showcase/slide-types/' | url }}" target="_blank">Open the showcase deck →</a>
    </div>

    <pre><code>npm run pres -- previews/decks/my-deck.md -o previews/decks/my-deck --pdf --png</code></pre>

    <div class="slidetype-grid">
      {% for s in slideTypes %}
        <div class="slidetype-card">
          <a class="slidetype-thumb" href="{{ ('/previews/showcase/slide-types/?slide=' + s.slideIndex) | url }}" target="_blank">
            <img src="{{ ('/previews/showcase/slide-types/slides/slide-0' + s.slideIndex + '.png') | url }}" alt="{{ s.label }} thumbnail" onerror="this.outerHTML='<div class=&quot;slidetype-thumb-missing&quot;>Run npm run build:assets to generate thumbnails</div>'">
          </a>
          <div class="slidetype-meta">
            <h3>{{ s.label }} <span class="slidetype-type"><code>@type: {{ s.type }}</code></span></h3>
            <p>{{ s.description }}</p>
            <pre class="slidetype-syntax"><code>{{ s.syntax }}</code></pre>
            <a class="slidetype-link" href="{{ ('/previews/showcase/slide-types/?slide=' + s.slideIndex) | url }}" target="_blank">View in showcase deck →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <h3>HTML passthrough + components</h3>
      <p>
        The <code>@type: html</code> slide hands the body to the viewer unchanged, so you can embed components
        from <code>brand/components/</code>. The canonical example is the radar chart on slide 7 of the showcase —
        a portable copy of the same chart used on the website quiz.
      </p>
      <p>
        Component files live in <code>brand/components/*.js</code> and are auto-copied into each deck's output directory
        so the viewer can load them via <code>&lt;script src="components/radar.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="footnote">
      Source: <code>previews/showcase/slide-types.md</code>. Regenerate thumbnails with <code>npm run build:assets</code>.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
